-- JAL Seeks Early Retirement From Extra 3,300 Workers This Year, Nikkei Says
-- Fergus Maguire
-- 2010-06-22T21:47:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/jal-seeks-early-retirement-from-extra-3-300-workers-this-year-nikkei-says.html

          
          
             Japan Airlines Corp. will seek early
retirement for an extra 3,300 workers in the year ending March,
Kyodo News said, citing sources familiar with the matter. As of
early this month, about 4,000 employees had applied for early
retirement, the report said.  
          
          


  


        